Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @Goat's Cheese{100%grams} into rounds. Halve the @Ciabatta{2}.

Spread the cheese over each piece of ciabatta and pop onto a lined #baking tray{}. Season with @Pepper{to taste} and a drizzle of @Oil{to taste}.

Bake on the top shelf until the bread is toasted and the cheese is melted, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, thinly slice the @Tomato{2}(thinly sliced). Roughly chop the @Hazelnuts{10%grams}(roughly chopped).

Trim and roughly chop the @Salad Leaves{120%grams}(roughly chopped).

Trim the @Cucumber{1}(halved lengthways, then chopped widthways into thin semicircles).

In a #salad bowl{}, toss together tomatoes, salad leaves, nuts, cucumber and @Honey Mustard Dressing{1%sachet}.

Season with @Salt{to taste} and @Pepper{to taste}.

Divide the salad between #plates{}.

Serve the goat's cheese ciabatta alongside.

> A wonderfully crusty ciabatta covered in melted goat's cheese accompanies a honey mustard salad packed with fresh veg.